<p style="text-align: center;">The link for interviews with local schools will be in a separate email and will only be sent to students who have been approved for local placement. If you need a local placement, please<br /><br /> submit a Request for Exception to Policy form as quickly as possible&nbsp;by clicking <a href="https://byui.box.com/shared/static/e228637a76c262307ea2.pdf">HERE</a>.<br /><br /> Either email the form to <a href="mailto:fieldservices@byui.edu">fieldservices@byui.edu</a> or bring it to Hinckley 325.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><br /><br /></p>
<hr />
<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;&nbsp; <br /><br /> <strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Basic Info about the Interviews</span></strong><br />&nbsp; </p>
<ul>
<li style="text-align: center;">&nbsp; If you will not be in the Southeast Idaho area on these dates, we highly recommend that you find a way to come. If you are unable to attend, Google+ interviews will be arranged (further information about this later).</li>
</ul>
<ul style="text-align: center;">
<li>&nbsp; This is the time when you will interview with principals for your student teaching placement.</li>
</ul>
<ul style="text-align: center;">
<li>&nbsp; Your student teaching placement will largely be determined by your interviews and wish list.</li>
</ul>
<ul style="text-align: center;">
<li>&nbsp; You will submit your school/location wish list after you complete your interviews. The wish lists will be at the welcome table when you arrive to sign in for your interviews.</li>
</ul>
<ul style="text-align: center;">
<li>&nbsp; Click <a href="Documents/education-human-dev/Field_Services_Office/Student Wish List.docx">HERE</a> for wish list.</li>
</ul>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<hr />
<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;<br /><br /> <strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">How to Prepare</span></strong><br />&nbsp;</p>
<ul>
<li>&nbsp; Mark these dates on your calendar: January 27<sup>th</sup>, 28<sup>th</sup>, and 29<sup>th</sup>, 2014</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>&nbsp; Start preparing your resume</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>&nbsp; Print your personal bio (that the Field Services Office emailed you upon completion) and your resume. If you do not have a copy of your personal bio, email <a href="mailto:fieldservices@byui.edu">fieldservices@byui.edu</a> to request a copy.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>&nbsp; Bring your practicum name tag, along with several copies of your resume and personal bio, to your interviews</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>&nbsp; Watch for an email &nbsp;January 2014 about how to sign up for the interviews</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>&nbsp; To research the schools that will be represented, click <a href="x19583.xml">HERE</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p style="text-align: center;"><br /> The link for interviews with local schools will be in a separate email and will only be sent to students who have been approved for local placement. If you need a local placement, please submit a Request for Exception to Policy form as quickly as possible&nbsp;by clicking <a href="https://byui.box.com/shared/static/e228637a76c262307ea2.pdf">HERE</a>.<br /><br /> Either email the form to <a href="mailto:fieldservices@byui.edu">fieldservices@byui.edu</a> or bring it to Hinckley 325.</p>
